pulls/25133","html_url":"https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/25133","diff_url":"https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/25133.diff","patch_url":"https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/25133.patch","merged_at":null},"body":"gh-21670 reported that the documentation of `np.var` and `np.std` should include important terms like "sample variance"/"sample standard deviation" and "Bessel correction" to help users choose the appropriate `ddof` for their application. (It also reported a misunderstanding about how the "mean" was calculated, but this appears to have been ameliorated with the word "average" since the issue was opened.)

